.1 Availability of Issuance Records

.11 The CWD shall maintain issuance and reconciliation records for a period of three years from the month of origin. This period may be extended at the written request of FNS.

.12 Issuance records shall include, at a minimum:

(a) Notices of Action;

(b) The DFA 286;

(c) Transacted authorizing documents;

(d) The FNS-250 and substantiating documents;

(e) The DFA 293;

(f) The DFA 289;

(g) Master issuance files;

(h) Records-for-issuance for each month; and

(i) Any roster or lists produced by issuance systems.

.13 In lieu of the records, easily retrievable microfilm, microfiche, or computer tapes which contain the required information may be maintained.

.2 Security and Control of Issuance and Accountable Documents

.21 Issuance Documents

The CWD shall control all issuance documents which establish household eligibility while the documents are transferred and processed within the county. These issuance documents include access devices and numbered transaction receipts if used in an automated direct access issuance system. The CWD shall use numbers, batching, inventory control logs or similar controls from the point of initial receipt through the issuance and reconciliation process. The CWD shall also insure the security and control of authorization documents in transit from the manufacturer to the county welfare office.

